{k1, k2,...}\\[Subset]{1,2,...,n} in the fermionic Gaussian state \
characterized by n*n matrix grn of single-particle Green's function. \
WickLogarithmicNegativity[ws,{k1,k2,...}] calculates the logarithmic \
negativity for the Wick state (fermionic Gaussian pure state without pairing \
correlation) ws. WickLogarithmicNegativity[data, {k1, k2, ...}] calculates \
the logarithmic negativities of elements of data, which may be an array of \
Green's function matices or Wick states.", "synonyms" -> {}, 
